# Defense-in-depth: a hold exactly consumed by settles is reaped AT SETTLE TIME — no remaining=0
# tombstone lingers waiting for a terminal release that may never arrive. Proof in-stream:
#   1. two 0.5 BTC settles exactly consume both orders' holds;
#   2. the subsequent RELEASEs find no hold -> silent idempotent no-ops (no BALANCE echo);
#   3. SNAPSHOT round-trips the (smaller) hold-free state;
#   4. re-HOLDing orderId=1 in a DIFFERENT asset is ACCEPTED as a fresh reservation — against a
#      lingering tombstone (assetId=BTC) it would be rejected as a cross-asset top-up.
CLOCK 1000
DEPOSIT u=100 asset=1 amt=1.0
DEPOSIT u=200 asset=0 amt=60000.0
HOLD order=1 u=100 asset=1 amt=1.0
HOLD order=2 u=200 asset=0 amt=60000.0
SETTLE tradeId=1 market=1 takerOrder=2 takerUser=200 makerOrder=1 makerUser=100 px=60000.0 qty=0.5 takerBuy=1
SETTLE tradeId=2 market=1 takerOrder=2 takerUser=200 makerOrder=1 makerUser=100 px=60000.0 qty=0.5 takerBuy=1
RELEASE order=1 u=100
RELEASE order=2 u=200
SNAPSHOT
HOLD order=1 u=100 asset=0 amt=1000.0
